description: Returns the default engine and system parameter information for the cluster database engine.

parameters.name: DBParameterGroupFamily
parameters.description: The name of the cluster parameter group family to return the engine parameter information for.

parameters.name: Filters
parameters.description: This parameter is not currently supported. (dict) --- A named set of filter values, used to return a more specific list of results. You can use a filter to match a set of resources by specific criteria, such as IDs. Wildcards are not supported in filters. The name of the filter. Filter names are case sensitive. One or more filter values. Filter values are case sensitive. (string) ---

nested_params.name: Name
nested_params.description: The name of the filter. Filter names are case sensitive.

nested_params.name: Values
nested_params.description: One or more filter values. Filter values are case sensitive.

parameters.name: MaxRecords
parameters.description: The maximum number of records to include in the response. If more records exist than the specified MaxRecords value, a pagination token (marker) is included in the response so that the remaining results can be retrieved. Default: 100 Constraints: Minimum 20, maximum 100.

nested_items.name: EngineDefaults
nested_items.description: Contains the result of a successful invocation of the DescribeEngineDefaultClusterParameters operation.

nested_items.name: DBParameterGroupFamily
nested_items.description: The name of the cluster parameter group family to return the engine parameter information for.

nested_items.name: Marker
nested_items.description: An optional pagination token provided by a previous request. If this parameter is specified, the response includes only records beyond the marker, up to the value specified by MaxRecords.

nested_items.name: Parameters
nested_items.description: The parameters of a particular cluster parameter group family.

nested_items.name: ParameterName
nested_items.description: Specifies the name of the parameter.

nested_items.name: ParameterValue
nested_items.description: Specifies the value of the parameter.

nested_items.name: Description
nested_items.description: Provides a description of the parameter.

nested_items.name: Source
nested_items.description: Indicates the source of the parameter value.

nested_items.name: DataType
nested_items.description: Specifies the valid data type for the parameter.

nested_items.name: AllowedValues
nested_items.description: Specifies the valid range of values for the parameter.

nested_items.name: IsModifiable
nested_items.description: Indicates whether ( true) or not ( false) the parameter can be modified. Some parameters have security or operational implications that prevent them from being changed.

nested_items.name: MinimumEngineVersion
nested_items.description: The earliest engine version to which the parameter can apply.

nested_items.name: ApplyMethod
nested_items.description: Indicates when to apply parameter updates.
